      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the chips to a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>curry powder </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>spiced chips</strong></p>",
